<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="558" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1611,1996]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1611,1636]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556">Description.</emphasis>
Description based on 
<typeStatus box="[596,698,1611,1636]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556">holotype</typeStatus>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[708,1013,1611,1635]" family="Chaetonotidae" genus="Heterolepidoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="mariae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[708,1013,1611,1635]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="556">Heterolepidoderma mariae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1021,1110,1611,1636]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1021,1110,1611,1636]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is a small-sized species, 
<number box="[1394,1436,1612,1636]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="138.0">138</number>
Μm in total body length (
<figureCitation box="[428,530,1647,1672]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 2" captionStart-1="FIGURE 3" captionStart-2="FIGURE 4" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,1914,1936]" captionStartId-1="5.[151,250,1518,1540]" captionStartId-2="6.[151,250,1843,1865]" captionTargetBox-0="[170,1416,205,1892]" captionTargetBox-1="[237,1376,750,1472]" captionTargetBox-2="[453,1132,481,1820]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[170,1417,193,1892]" captionTargetId-1="figure@5.[210,1396,748,1480]" captionTargetId-2="figure@6.[453,1134,481,1821]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionTargetPageId-2="6" captionText-0="FIGURE 2. Photos of some sampling sites for the present study. A) Biribiri State Park, Diamantina, State of Minas Gerais. B) Sempre-Vivas Federal Park, Diamantina, State of Minas Gerais. C – D) urban lagoon, Paulínia, State of São Paulo." captionText-1="FIGURE 3. Schematic drawings of Heterolepidoderma mariae sp. nov. A) Dorsal view. B) Ventral view. The scales are not in scale. Scale bars: 25 Μm." captionText-2="FIGURE 4. Heterolepidoderma mariae sp. nov. holotype. DIC photomicrographs: A) Habitus. B) Dorsal view of distribution and shape of scales. C) Ventral view showing the paired keeled scales at the base of the furca. D) Ventral view showing the interciliary scales. E) Ventral view showing the connection between the parallel rows of cilia. Scale bars: 22 Μm." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/235115/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/235116/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/235117/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="556">
Figs 
<number box="[484,530,1647,1671]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Head is three-lobed, epipleurae more developed than hypopleurae. Cephalion 
<number box="[1422,1436,1647,1671]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="9.0">9</number>
Μm in width. Hypostomium 
<number box="[471,506,1683,1708]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="9.5">9.5</number>
Μm in width, well developed without anterior teeth, upper part straight, lower part concave (
<figureCitation box="[263,346,1719,1744]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1843,1865]" captionTargetBox="[453,1132,481,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[453,1134,481,1821]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Heterolepidoderma mariae sp. nov. holotype. DIC photomicrographs: A) Habitus. B) Dorsal view of distribution and shape of scales. C) Ventral view showing the paired keeled scales at the base of the furca. D) Ventral view showing the interciliary scales. E) Ventral view showing the connection between the parallel rows of cilia. Scale bars: 22 Μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235117/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="556">
Figs. 
<number box="[331,346,1719,1743]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
E; 
<number box="[381,396,1719,1744]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="5.0">5</number>
B; 
<number box="[434,448,1719,1744]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="6.0">6</number>
A–B). One pair of cephalic ciliary tufts with two different sizes of cilia: 8, 15 Μm, respectively. Ocellar granules absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1611,1996]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556">
Body width 
<number box="[337,365,1791,1815]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="22.0">22</number>
Μm at the head (U 
<number box="[574,603,1791,1815]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="10.0">10</number>
), 
<number box="[623,651,1791,1815]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="20.0">20</number>
Μm at the neck (U 
<number box="[859,889,1791,1816]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="25.0">25</number>
), 
<number box="[908,936,1791,1815]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="29.0">29</number>
Μm at the trunk (U 
<number box="[1149,1178,1791,1816]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="54.0">54</number>
) and 
<number box="[1241,1269,1791,1815]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="13.0">13</number>
Μm at the base of the furca (U 
<number box="[323,353,1828,1852]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="80.0">80</number>
). Head slightly delimited from trunk by neck constriction that gradually widens into the trunk, which reaches its greatest width around U 
<number box="[630,702,1863,1888]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="47.5" valueMax="50.0" valueMin="45.0">45–50</number>
. The trunk then tapers into a straight furca, 
<number box="[1203,1217,1864,1887]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="7.0">7</number>
Μm in length, with rather thin adhesive tubes, 
<number box="[456,505,1899,1924]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="13.5">13.5</number>
Μm in length, pointing slightly outward at their distal ends. Base of furca covered dorsolaterally, laterally and ventrally with keeled scales. Anterior and posterior sensory bristles present, anterior pair at U 
<number box="[249,319,1971,1996]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="26.5" valueMax="27.0" valueMin="26.0">26–27</number>
anchored by papillae and posterior pair at U 
<number box="[818,845,1972,1996]" pageId="5" pageNumber="556" value="84.0">84</number>
anchored by double-keeled scales.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">
Dorsal body surface covered by 
<number box="[565,635,152,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="21.0" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="20.0">20–22</number>
longitudinal rows of 
<number box="[878,948,152,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="36.0" valueMax="38.0" valueMin="34.0">34–38</number>
keeled scales with visible edges (
<figureCitation box="[1330,1407,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1518,1540]" captionTargetBox="[237,1376,750,1472]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[210,1396,748,1480]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Schematic drawings of Heterolepidoderma mariae sp. nov. A) Dorsal view. B) Ventral view. The scales are not in scale. Scale bars: 25 Μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235116/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">
Figs. 
<number box="[1394,1407,152,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A; 
<number box="[151,167,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="4.0">4</number>
B; 
<number box="[202,216,188,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="5.0">5</number>
A; 
<number box="[255,269,188,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="6.0">6</number>
C–F). The median row of dorsal scales is straight, except in the narrowest part of the neck and the rearmost trunk region, where it is replaced by 
<number box="[663,725,223,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4 to 6</number>
rows of diagonally arranged scales. Three different dorsal scale shapes: a) head scales small, oval with trilobate keels, 
<number box="[758,842,260,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="2.4" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.3">2.3–2.5</number>
Μm in length and 
<number box="[1043,1127,260,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="1.75" valueMax="2.1" valueMin="1.4">1.4–2.1</number>
Μm in width (
<figureCitation box="[1284,1360,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1518,1540]" captionTargetBox="[237,1376,750,1472]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[210,1396,748,1480]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Schematic drawings of Heterolepidoderma mariae sp. nov. A) Dorsal view. B) Ventral view. The scales are not in scale. Scale bars: 25 Μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235116/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">
Figs. 
<number box="[1347,1360,260,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A; 
<number box="[1396,1412,260,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="4.0">4</number>
B; 
<number box="[151,165,295,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="5.0">5</number>
A; 
<number box="[203,218,295,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="6.0">6</number>
C); b) trunk scales elongate-oval with slight constriction in the median region, straight posterior end and trilobate keels, 
<number box="[331,373,332,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6</number>
Μm in length and 
<number box="[599,662,332,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2</number>
Μm in width (
<figureCitation box="[838,919,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1518,1540]" captionTargetBox="[237,1376,750,1472]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[210,1396,748,1480]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Schematic drawings of Heterolepidoderma mariae sp. nov. A) Dorsal view. B) Ventral view. The scales are not in scale. Scale bars: 25 Μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235116/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">
Figs. 
<number box="[906,919,332,356]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A; 
<number box="[959,975,332,356]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="4.0">4</number>
B; 
<number box="[1011,1025,332,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="5.0">5</number>
A; 
<number box="[1064,1078,332,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="6.0">6</number>
D–E); c) posterior body scales elongate-oval with fine keels drawing out into simple fine spines, 
<number box="[915,929,367,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="5.0">5</number>
Μm in length and 
<number box="[1146,1160,368,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="2.0">2</number>
Μm in width (
<figureCitation box="[1328,1407,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1518,1540]" captionTargetBox="[237,1376,750,1472]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[210,1396,748,1480]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Schematic drawings of Heterolepidoderma mariae sp. nov. A) Dorsal view. B) Ventral view. The scales are not in scale. Scale bars: 25 Μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235116/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">
Figs. 
<number box="[1394,1407,368,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A; 
<number box="[151,166,404,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" value="6.0">6</number>
D,F).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235117/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" targetBox="[453,1132,481,1820]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1843,1926]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1843,1865]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[282,558,1843,1865]" family="Chaetonotidae" genus="Heterolepidoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="mariae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[282,558,1843,1865]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">Heterolepidoderma mariae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[564,646,1843,1864]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[564,646,1843,1864]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
holotype. DIC photomicrographs: A) Habitus. B) Dorsal view of distribution and shape of scales. C) Ventral view showing the paired keeled scales at the base of the furca. D) Ventral view showing the interciliary scales. E) Ventral view showing the connection between the parallel rows of cilia. Scale bars: 22 Μm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235118/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" targetBox="[150,1436,193,1407]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1430,1482]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1430,1452]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">FIGURE 5.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[281,556,1430,1452]" family="Chaetonotidae" genus="Heterolepidoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="mariae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[281,556,1430,1452]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">Heterolepidoderma mariae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[562,642,1430,1451]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[562,642,1430,1451]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
paratype. DIC photomicrographs: A) Dorsal view of distribution and shape of scales. B) Ventral view of distribution and shape of scales and cilia. White arrow indicates hypostomium. Scale bars: 22 Μm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1522,2014]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">
The interciliary area is covered by 
<number box="[602,644,1522,1547]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
longitudinal rows of 
<number box="[893,921,1522,1546]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" value="14.0">14</number>
elliptical keeled scales with short spines (
<number pageId="7" pageNumber="558" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1– 1.5</number>
Μm), in each longitudinal row, with pharyngeal field portion naked. The last posterior row (including ventral terminal scales) consists of four larger keeled scales, with two different sizes (approximately 2,5 and 
<number box="[1342,1356,1594,1619]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" value="5.0">5</number>
Μm in length). Ventral ciliation appears as two longitudinal bands that merge on the head, forming a transverse band of cilia (
<figureCitation box="[214,291,1666,1691]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1518,1540]" captionTargetBox="[237,1376,750,1472]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[210,1396,748,1480]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Schematic drawings of Heterolepidoderma mariae sp. nov. A) Dorsal view. B) Ventral view. The scales are not in scale. Scale bars: 25 Μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235116/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">
Figs. 
<number box="[277,291,1666,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B; 
<number box="[325,339,1666,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" value="4.0">4</number>
C–D; 
<number box="[407,422,1666,1691]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" value="5.0">5</number>
B; 
<number box="[454,469,1666,1691]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" value="6.0">6</number>
A,B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1522,2014]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">
Mouth subterminal, 
<number box="[428,491,1701,1726]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" value="5.2" valueMax="6.4" valueMin="4.0">4–6.4</number>
Μm in diameter; pharynx 
<number box="[786,857,1701,1726]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" value="36.5" valueMax="38.0" valueMin="35.0">35–38</number>
Μm in length with anterior and posterior swellings. Anterior region of pharynx without cuticular rods.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1522,2014]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">
Some specimens were in parthenogenetic phase, with the egg (
<number box="[908,979,1773,1798]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" value="63.5" valueMax="67.0" valueMin="60.0">60–67</number>
Μm in length) positioned laterally in the trunk region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="559" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1522,2014]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="559" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1845,1870]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[455,673,1846,1870]" family="Chaetonotidae" genus="Heterolepidoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[455,673,1846,1870]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">Heterolepidoderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes 
<number box="[788,816,1846,1870]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" value="22.0">22</number>
species that inhabit inland water. Among them, only 
<taxonomicName box="[151,460,1882,1906]" family="Chaetonotidae" genus="Heterolepidoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="mariae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,460,1882,1906]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">Heterolepidoderma mariae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[473,567,1882,1907]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[473,567,1882,1907]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<emphasis box="[586,921,1882,1906]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">
<taxonomicName box="[586,696,1883,1906]" family="Chaetonotidae" genus="Heterolepidoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="majus">H. majus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kisielewski, 1981" authorityName="Kisielewski" authorityYear="1981" box="[712,921,1882,1906]" family="Chaetonotidae" genus="Heterolepidoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="brevitubulatum">H. brevitubulatum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kisielewski" box="[933,1141,1882,1907]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" refString="Kisielewski, J. (1981) Gastrotricha from raised and transitional peat bogs in Poland. Monografie Fauny Polski, 11, 1 - 143. [Polska Akademia Nauk, Warszawa]" type="journal article" year="1981">
Kisielewski, 
<number box="[1085,1141,1882,1906]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" value="1981.0">1981</number>
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1205,1346,1883,1906]" family="Chaetonotidae" genus="Heterolepidoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="jureiense">
<emphasis box="[1205,1346,1883,1906]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">H. jureiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a clearly three-lobed head. 
<taxonomicName box="[448,588,1919,1942]" family="Chaetonotidae" genus="Heterolepidoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="jureiense">
<emphasis box="[448,588,1919,1942]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">H. jureiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be excluded from further comparison as it is the only species with ventrolateral lamellae among these four species. 
<taxonomicName box="[702,1098,1954,1978]" family="Chaetonotidae" genus="Heterolepidoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="brevitubulatum">
<emphasis box="[702,1098,1954,1978]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">Heterolepidoderma brevitubulatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has adhesive tubes extremely short and slightly bifurcate, whereas in 
<taxonomicName box="[606,721,1991,2014]" family="Chaetonotidae" genus="Heterolepidoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="mariae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[606,721,1991,2014]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">H. mariae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[731,822,1989,2014]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,822,1989,2014]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[881,984,1991,2014]" family="Chaetonotidae" genus="Heterolepidoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="majus">
<emphasis box="[881,984,1991,2014]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="558">H. majus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the adhesive tubes are at least 
<number box="[1352,1366,1990,2014]" pageId="7" pageNumber="558" value="4.0">4</number>
times longer and not bifurcate. 
<taxonomicName box="[436,741,152,176]" family="Chaetonotidae" genus="Heterolepidoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="8" pageNumber="559" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="mariae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[436,741,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="559">Heterolepidoderma mariae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[750,840,151,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="559" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[750,840,151,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="559">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[1148,1251,152,176]" family="Chaetonotidae" genus="Heterolepidoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="8" pageNumber="559" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="majus">
<emphasis box="[1148,1251,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="559">H. majus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because it has a dorsal body surface covered by keeled scales with three different shapes, as well as a transverse band of cilia on the head connecting the two bands of longitudinal ventral cilia, whereas 
<taxonomicName box="[916,1017,224,248]" family="Chaetonotidae" genus="Heterolepidoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="8" pageNumber="559" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="majus">
<emphasis box="[916,1017,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="559">H. majus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only one 
<typeStatus box="[1171,1219,224,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="559">type</typeStatus>
of keeled scales on its dorsal surface, and its two ventral bands of cilia separate.
</paragraph>
